cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.MS, cs.LG, cs.CR 

The paper discusses defect growth and structural patterns in a software system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The system is written in Fortran, which is a programming language (cs.PL). The paper also discusses software metrics and their correlations, which falls under the category of measurement and analysis of software (cs.MS). The analysis of long-term data and the re-calibration of generalizations also suggest a machine learning aspect (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses defect clustering, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
